gvSIG-i18n RELEASE NOTES
========================


version 2.1.4

Bug fix: Restored tool method fElaborarInformeModulos, that was accidentally removed in previous release.


|
|

------------------------------------------------

version 2.1.4

Addition: Added 2011 year to the copyright notice to files generated by ArchGenXML.
Addition: Translations page: Added to confirmation dialogs a message indicating that the user may disable the confirmation dialogs with a check box in the Options section.
Bug fix:  Fixed bug in TRACatalogo_Retrieval methods to access the first collection of a certain type, which failed when no collections were present, causing a failure when deleting a translations catalog.
Bug fix:  When loading translations interchange contents from GNU gettext .POT files, if no Default string is supplied in the entry, the symbol for the entry is used as the translation for the default language (usually [en]).
Change:   When loading translations interchange contents from a .zip archive, the entries are created under the TRAImportacion element, in the same order as the files read (previously the entries were created sorted by language, then module).
Change:   Make most String and Text fields non-searcheable - except description and text, to avoid excessive growth of main database (Data.fs), because of the growth of portal_catalog. Specifically, the text field holding translations interchange content impact heavily on Data.fs, while they shouldn't.
Change:   In Translations catalog root page, display contributing users in as few lines as possible. (previously, each user displayed in a separate line).

|
|

------------------------------------------------

version 2.1.3

Fixed bug: In the translations page, when enabled the option to show the status change buttons, for batch mode, when hiding or dusplaying the symbols column, and displaying or hiding the columns in a row over the translations, the grid looses its proper arrangement, because some cells are not properly hidden or shown. 
Addition: Translations page now show the string sources (files where the string is used) in the editor details. String sources field now added to TRATraduccion, and to the metadata held in indexes to search for TRATraduccion.
Addition: When unauthorized users request the rendering of a Status Report (Summary by Languages, or by Modules and Languages) or Activity Report, ths system informe the user that he/she has no permission to generate the report.
Addition: The rendering of a Status Report (Summary by Languages, or by Modules and Languages) or Activity Report, now includes a hyperlink to the last Status (or Contributions) Report.
Addition: Status Reports now present two distinct views, to display the Summary Report by Languages and other for the Report by Modules and Languages. The Tabular view of the Report no longer embeds the presentatios of these two reports, but rather ender a hyperlink to visit the specific report view.
Addition: Initial page of translations catalog now presents the contributing users and administrators of the catalog.

